.TH "AUDIOWORKLETPROCESSOR.PARAMETERDESCRIPTORS_STATIC" "3JS" "July 12, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
AudioWorkletProcessor.parameterDescriptors_static \-
AudioWorkletProcessor: parameterDescriptors static property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The read\-only \f[B]\f[CB]parameterDescriptors\f[B]\f[R] property of an
\f[CR]AudioWorkletProcessor\f[R]\-derived class is a \f[I]static
getter\f[R], which returns an iterable of
\f[CR]AudioParamDescriptor\f[R]\-based objects.
.PP
The property is not a part of the \f[CR]AudioWorkletProcessor\f[R]
interface, but, if defined, it is called internally by the
\f[CR]AudioWorkletProcessor\f[R] constructor to create a list of custom
\f[CR]AudioParam\f[R] objects in the \f[CR]parameters\f[R] property of
the associated \f[CR]AudioWorkletNode\f[R].
.PP
Defining the getter is optional.
.SH VALUE
An iterable of \f[CR]AudioParamDescriptor\f[R]\-based objects.
The properties of these objects are as follows:
.TP
\f[B]name\f[R]
The string which represents the name of the \f[CR]AudioParam\f[R].
Under this name the \f[CR]AudioParam\f[R] will be available in the
\f[CR]parameters\f[R] property of the node, and under this name the
\f[CR]AudioWorkletProcessor.process\f[R] method will acquire the
calculated values of this \f[CR]AudioParam\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]automationRate\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Either \f[CR]\(dqa\-rate\(dq\f[R], or \f[CR]\(dqk\-rate\(dq\f[R] string
which represents an automation rate of this \f[CR]AudioParam\f[R].
Defaults to \f[CR]\(dqa\-rate\(dq\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]minValue\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A \f[CR]float\f[R] which represents minimum value of the
\f[CR]AudioParam\f[R].
Defaults to \f[CR]\-3.4028235e38\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]maxValue\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A \f[CR]float\f[R] which represents maximum value of the
\f[CR]AudioParam\f[R].
Defaults to \f[CR]3.4028235e38\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]defaultValue\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A \f[CR]float\f[R] which represents initial value of the
\f[CR]AudioParam\f[R].
Defaults to \f[CR]0\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
See \f[CR]AudioWorkletNode.parameters\f[R] for example code showing how
to add static \f[CR]parameterDescriptors\f[R] getter to a custom
\f[CR]AudioWorkletProcessor\f[R].
.SH SEE ALSO
